## .NET / Visual Studio

# Local scratch folder
.scratch/

# Build results
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/
x64/
x86/
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/

# Exception: Bridge.exe + deps at repo root are checked in so /plugin install
# can launch the MCP server straight after Claude Code clones the marketplace
# repo. Refreshed by scripts/Build-Release.ps1. *.pdb stays excluded globally.
!/bin/
!/bin/**

# Exception: SharedAssemblies.Config.json is checked in because it is the
# source of truth for which assemblies DevReload must stream into the default
# (non-collectible) ALC. A fresh clone + dotnet build won't produce this
# file, so without tracking it the v18 G6 fix (Acd.Mcp.Contracts split)
# silently regresses to the v17 broken state. See G8 in CRASH_TEST_V2_JOURNAL.md.
#
# Git's "ignored directory" rule means we have to un-ignore each level of
# the path explicitly, then re-ignore the directory contents, then un-ignore
# the one file. The result: only SharedAssemblies.Config.json is tracked
# inside the otherwise-ignored bin/ trees.
!src/Acd.Mcp/bin/
src/Acd.Mcp/bin/*
!src/Acd.Mcp/bin/Debug/
!src/Acd.Mcp/bin/Release/
src/Acd.Mcp/bin/Debug/*
src/Acd.Mcp/bin/Release/*
!src/Acd.Mcp/bin/Debug/SharedAssemblies.Config.json
!src/Acd.Mcp/bin/Release/SharedAssemblies.Config.json
[Ll]og/
[Ll]ogs/
bld/
artifacts/

